RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 1 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 45. Maiden Claiming Purse 14400. FOR ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA-BRED MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE, FOUR, FIVE, AND SIX YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $7,500, if for $7,000, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: JUJU ON DA BEAT gave chase and raced two deep on the turn, dug in under steady stretch handling, took the lead in later yards and was drawing away toward the wire. BOWMANS LAZY GIRL set a pressured pace from the half mile pole, rounded the turn at the rail and was steadily encouraged through the lane, but gave up the lead while flattening stride in later yards. VIESTE gave chase through the backstretch, raced off the rail on the turn, eased out entering the stretch, angled to the rail leaving the eighth pole, altered course from tight quarters at the rail in later yards and held on for third. JUNIPER GRACE gave chase, rounded the turn at the rail, was shut off on the heels of Vieste past the eighth pole, recovered stride from that point but was shut off again by that one in later yards and flattened stride. PRETTY CASTLE gave chase from well back, improved at the rail on the turn, eased outward through the stretch and finished evenly. MIRACLE SONDE became fractious and flipped in the paddock, gave chase through the backstretch, raced in the five path of the turn then flattened in the lane. JUST ASK ME pressured the pace through the backstretch then weakened in the four path of the turn. The Stewards reviewed a claim of foul against the rider of Vieste for interference leaving the eighth pole and again in late stretch, lodged by the rider of Juniper Grace, and as a result, the former was disqualified to fourth place.

ENTRY.NAME: Pretty Castle
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased,improved rail turn,eased out lane,even finish

ENTRY.NAME: dq-Vieste
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased,off rail turn,angled in past 1/8,angled out late,held 3rd

ENTRY.NAME: Juniper Grace
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased,rail turn,shut off past 1/8 and later yards

ENTRY.NAME: Juju On Da Beat
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased,2d turn,closed steadily,up later yards,drew away

ENTRY.NAME: Bowmans Lazy Girl
ENTRY.COMMENT: set pressured pace,rail turn,caught later yards

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 2 7F Dirt CR: 54. Claiming Purse 12000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since June 8 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs. NO WVB CLAUSE.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HOVEL angled in and saved ground racing well back from early contention, edged closer through the backstretch, started a bid nearing the quarter pole and improved at the rail on the far turn, took the lead past the eighth pole and held on while drifting steadily to the outside through the lane. LADY WHISTLEDOWN saved ground on the first turn and settled off the pace, bid leaving the seven sixteenths pole, angled to the four path approaching the head of the lane and was outfinished while being carried outward through the lane. JACCACI settled off the rail on the first turn, picked up the chase leaving the three eighths pole and dueled at even terms midway on the far turn, but was shut off at the heels of Hovel mid-stretch and flattened the final sixteenth. CURLIN'S DOVE moved to the inside and rated the pace, came under pressure leaving the seven sixteenths pole, was met at even terms midway on the far turn then flattened the final sixteenth. PRETTY SPECTACULAR raced in the three and four paths on the first turn, bid leaving the seven sixteenths pole but weakened off the rail on the far turn. BESTLA rated close early, gave chase from the seven sixteenths pole then faded off the rail on the far turn.

ENTRY.OWNER: Brown Nicole and Brown Ronney W
ENTRY.COMMENT: off rail,chased 3/8,even terms mid turn,shut off 1/16,flattened

RACE.FOOTNOTES: VOICE OF NOW rated the pace inside, came under pressure approaching the quarter pole, raced off the rail on the far turn, drifted in the upper stretch but held well with steady handling. TAP SECRET saved ground, bid leaving the seven sixteenths pole and rounded the far turn off the rail, though flattened later yards. MR MAJESTIC settled off the rail, picked up the chase nearing the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the turn in the three path and came along to take third the final strides. MIMS SECOND CHANCE raced with the early pace then stalked on the first turn, gave chase past the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn near the rail and flattened in the stretch. DANNY'S WINKSTER settled in the three path the first turn, gave chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole but faded on the far turn. SMOKIN SMITTY rated close inside on the opening turn, picked up the chase nearing the three eighths pole but faded into the far turn.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 4 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 67. Claiming Purse 18500. FOR ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA-BRED THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since June 8 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000, For Each $1,000 To $8,000 1 lb. (Races Whe re Entered For $6,250 Or Less Not Considered In Weight Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: NOW HOOK'EM angled in and rated the pace, contested the advantage near the rail on the turn and was steadily handled in the lane. TWO ROOM SCHOOL chased through the backstretch and contested at a close disadvantage in the three path on the turn, finished well, but settled for second. FOREVER TAKES TIME chased and raced two deep on the turn, dueled through the stretch and just held the nod for third. REATA'S CASTLE gave chase through the backstretch, rounded the turn in the four path, dug in leaving the turn and just missed the nod for third. BEAR'S ESTATE chased inside, checked in tight at the rail leaving the five sixteenths pole, recovered stride past the quarter, raced off the rail on the turn and weakened in the lane. CHIPPEWA'S CASTLE steadied in tight on the chute then saved ground. The Stewards reviewed, then rejected, a claim of foul against the rider of Now Hook'em for alleged interference in the vicinity of the five sixteenths pole, lodged by the rider of Bear's Estate.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: JEFFERSON NATIVE set a pressured pace, contested even terms two deep on the turn and dug in determinedly to eke out the nod over the game challenge of ENTRY TIME, who gave chase, dueled to even terms three wide toward the eighth pole and dug in gamely to the wire. THE ILLUSIONIST chased inside, raced off the rail on the turn and flattened inside the sixteenth pole. RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 6 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 66. Claiming Purse 17500. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since June 8 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000, For Each $1,000 To $8,000 1 lb. (Races Where Entered For $6,250 Or Less Not Considered In Weight Allowances) NO WVB CLAUSE.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: QUEEN CASHMERE dueled for the lead toward the seven sixteenths pole and set a pressured pace, contested the rail through the turn and held on under steady handling. RUNNING FREE gave chase, raced at the rail on the turn and dug in to take second later yards while gaining on the winner. TWO STEP SALLY pressured the pace inside, raced close at the rail on the turn, eased out leaving the turn and relented in the stretch duel for second. BAYLIS STREET pressured the pace three wide, dropped back in the three path approaching the top of the stretch and weakened the final sixteenth. BROADWAY PEGGY gave chase, raced in the three path on the turn and weakened in the lane. MIDNIGHT PASS pressured the pace four wide through the backstretch but dropped back approaching the quarter pole and weakened five wide on the turn.

ENTRY.COMMENT: set pressured pace,rail turn,held on driving

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 7 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 105. Allowance Purse 34800. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since June 8 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since May 8 Allowed 4 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $25,000 Or Less Not Considered In Weight Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CLASSIER closed to the lead three wide approaching the nine sixteenths pole and rated the pace, came under pressure leaving the five sixteenths, widened at the rail on the far turn and was kept alert through the stretch. OUTLIER saved ground just off the pace, gave chase leaving the three eighths pole, raced at the rail on the far turn, drifted leaving the turn and dueled through the stretch for second. NO CHANGE settled in the two and three paths the first turn, gave chase nearing the five sixteenths pole, raced two deep on the far turn and was outfinished in the stretch duel for second. DONTMESAWITHME stalked the earlier pace two deep, bid leaving the five sixteenths pole, raced in the four path of the far turn and ran evenly in the stretch. EASTERN BAY saved ground, picked up the chase approaching the three eighths pole, rounded the turn near the rail then flattened in the stretch. AL LOVES JOSIE set the early pace inside, was met nearing the nine sixteenths pole and stalked from that point, gave chase past the three eighths, rounded the far turn at the rail and weakened in the lane. SOUND OFF raced well back.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 8 7F Dirt CR: 86. Starter Allowance Purse 20700. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $5,000 OR LESS SINCE JULY 8, 2021. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since June 8 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since May 8 Allowed 4 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $8,000 Or Less Not Considered In Weight Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DANCER'S MELODY stalked the early leader two deep, took over past the half mile pole and rated the pace, raced clear approaching the three eighths pole, came under pressure into the far turn and held well under steady handling. VOLNAY was strung six wide into the first turn and left the turn outside, started a bid leaving the seven sixteenths pole, raced in range of the lead off the rail on the far turn but couldn't improve in the lane and had to settle for second best. TEQUILA FOG rated off the pace inside on the first turn, gave chase from the seven sixteenths pole and improved off the rail on the far turn, dueled to take third mid-stretch and held on. FLOATING BY saved ground racing well off the pace, gave chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole and improved in the three path of the far turn, dug in leaving the turn and just missed third. HIDDEN IDENTITY raced boxed at the rail on the first turn, picked up the chase nearing the three eighths pole and came between horses at the five sixteenths, rounded the far turn at the rail then flattened toward mid-stretch. SHERIFF'S KID raced in the three path the first turn and showed little response through the backstretch. MYGIDGETMARIE set the early pace inside, was met past the half mile pole and gave chase through the backstretch, but weakened at the rail on the far turn. GOLDEN SWEETS rated close in the three path the first turn, gave chase approaching the seven sixteenths pole but weakened nearing the far turn. SOMMER VELVET was strung five wide into the first turn then stalked into the backstretch, gave chase from the three eighths pole but weakened through the far turn.
